    "The early visibility of the heartbeat highlights the sensitivity of cardiovascular development to maternal factors, potentially elevating long-term risks of conditions like heart disease.",
    "This observation reinforces the necessity of early prenatal care and proactive maternal health management to reduce adverse programming effects.",
    "Figure 7:7Figure7: This set of 4D ultrasound images, taken at 7-8 weeks of gestation, illustrates the emergence of early anatomical features such as limb buds, a pulsating heart, and the first observable fetal movements.",
